TITLE: Defining a Cloud Function for Averaging Movie Ratings in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This Cloud Function calculates the average star rating for a given movie. It accepts a movie name as a parameter, queries the Review objects, and returns the average rating.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/cloudcode/cloud-code.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
Parse.Cloud.define("averageStars", async (request) => {
  const query = new Parse.Query("Review");
  query.equalTo("movie", request.params.movie);
  const results = await query.find();
  let sum = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i < results.length; ++i) {
    sum += results[i].get("stars");
  }
  return sum / results.length;
});
```

