TITLE: Configuring Server-wide Rate Limit in Parse
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set a server-wide rate limit in Parse Server, allowing a maximum of 200 requests per 15-minute window across all API routes. This is critical for preventing resource exhaustion and protecting server integrity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/common/security.md#2025-04-22_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const parseServer = new ParseServer({
  rateLimit: {
    requestPath: '*',
    requestTimeWindow: 15 * 60 * 1000,
    requestCount: 200,
  },
});
```

