TITLE: Subclassing Parse.Object Using ES6 Classes in JavaScript SDK
DESCRIPTION: This snippet introduces using ES6 class syntax for extending Parse.Object, providing modern subclassing support in JavaScript. It encapsulates initialization logic and adds instance and static methods. Requires Parse JavaScript SDK version 1.6.0 or higher. The Monster class includes a constructor, an instance method, and a static spawn method to generate new objects with specific attributes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/js/objects.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
