TITLE: Using $notInQuery to Find Comments on Posts without Images
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates the $notInQuery operator to find Comment objects where the related Post does not have an image field. The query returns comments whose post field points to Post objects that don't match the specified condition.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/rest/queries.md#2025-04-22_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
curl -X GET \
  -H "X-Parse-Application-Id: ${APPLICATION_ID}" \
  -H "X-Parse-REST-API-Key: ${REST_API_KEY}" \
  -G \
  --data-urlencode 'where={"post":{"$notInQuery":{"where":{"image":{"$exists":true}},"className":"Post"}}}' \
  https://YOUR.PARSE-SERVER.HERE/parse/classes/Comment
```

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import http.client
import json
import urllib.parse


connection = http.client.HTTPSConnection('YOUR.PARSE-SERVER.HERE', 443)
params = urllib.parse.urlencode({"where": json.dumps({
    "post": {
        "$notInQuery": {
            "where": {
                "image": {
                    "$exists": True
                }
            },
            "className": "Post"
        }
    }
})})
connection.connect()
connection.request('GET', '/parse/classes/Comment?%s' % params, '', {
    "X-Parse-Application-Id": "${APPLICATION_ID}",
    "X-Parse-REST-API-Key": "${REST_API_KEY}"
})
result = json.loads(connection.getresponse().read())
print(result)
```

