TITLE: Demonstrating ParseUser Security Policy in C#
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates the security policy of ParseUser objects. It shows that authenticated users can modify their own data, while attempts to modify user data without authentication will throw an exception.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/dotnet/users.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
var user = await ParseUser.LogInAsync("my_username", "my_password");
user.Username = "my_new_username"; // attempt to change username
await user.SaveAsync(); // This succeeds, since this user was
                        // authenticated on the device

ParseUser.LogOut();
// Get the user from a non-authenticated method
user = await ParseUser.Query.GetAsync(user.ObjectId);
user.Username = "another_username";

// This will throw an exception, since the ParseUser is not authenticated
await user.SaveAsync();
```

