TITLE: Querying Users with Hometown Teams Query in Parse Server
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to perform a complex query using the $select operator to find users whose hometown teams have winning records. The query uses a subquery to match users based on their hometown team's win percentage.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/rest/queries.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
curl -X GET \
  -H "X-Parse-Application-Id: ${APPLICATION_ID}" \
  -H "X-Parse-REST-API-Key: ${REST_API_KEY}" \
  -G \
  --data-urlencode 'where={"hometown":{"$select":{"query":{"className":"Team","where":{"winPct":{"$gt":0.5}}},"key":"city"}}}' \
  https://YOUR.PARSE-SERVER.HERE/parse/classes/_User
```

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import http.client
import json
import urllib.parse


connection = http.client.HTTPSConnection('YOUR.PARSE-SERVER.HERE', 443)
params = urllib.parse.urlencode({"where": json.dumps({
    "hometown": {
        "$select": {
            "query": {
                "className": "Team",
                "where": {
                    "winPct": {
                        "$gt": 0.5
                    }
                }
            },
            "key": "city"
        }
    }
})})
connection.connect()
connection.request('GET', '/parse/classes/_User?%s' % params, '', {
    "X-Parse-Application-Id": "${APPLICATION_ID}",
    "X-Parse-REST-API-Key": "${REST_API_KEY}"
})
result = json.loads(connection.getresponse().read())
print(result)
```

