TITLE: Adding Fields and Indexes to a Schema in Parse Server
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to add a new field (population) and an index (population_index) to an existing schema class called "City" using Parse Server's REST API. It requires application ID and master key authentication.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/rest/schemas.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
curl -X PUT \
  -H "X-Parse-Application-Id: ${APPLICATION_ID}" \
  -H "X-Parse-Master-Key: ${MASTER_KEY}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '
    {
      "className": "City",
      "fields": {
        "population": {
          "type": "Number"
        }
      },
      "indexes": {
        "population_index": {
          "population": 1
        }
