TITLE: Implementing Custom Row and Next Page Views in ParseQueryAdapter for Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to completely override the default row and next page view implementations in ParseQueryAdapter. It creates custom item views with colors defined by ParseObjects and a custom next page view.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/android/user-interface.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
@Override 
public View getItemView(ParseObject object, View v, ViewGroup parent) { 
  if (v == null) { 
    v = View.inflate(getContext(), R.layout.adapter_item, null); 
  } 
  v.setBackgroundColor(object.getInt("color")); 
  return v; 
} 

@Override 
public View getNextPageView(View v, ViewGroup parent) { 
  if (v == null) { 
    // R.layout.adapter_next_page contains an ImageView with a custom graphic 
    // and a TextView. 
    v = View.inflate(getContext(), R.layout.adapter_next_page, null); 
  } 
  TextView textView = (TextView) v.findViewById(R.id.nextPageTextViewId); 
  textView.setText("Loaded " + getCount() + " rows. Get more!"); 
  return v; 
}
```

