TITLE: Setting Cache Policy with ParseQuery in Java
DESCRIPTION: This Java snippet demonstrates how to set a cache policy for a ParseQuery using Parse SDK. It tries the network first, then falls back to the cache if the network is unavailable. Dependencies include Parse SDK and a configured Parse server environment. The method uses asynchronous querying with callbacks to handle the results.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/android/queries.md#2025-04-22_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
