TITLE: Counting Objects with Query Constraints in Python
DESCRIPTION: Python implementation for counting GameScore objects for a specific player without retrieving results. Uses the count parameter with limit=0 to efficiently get only the count value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/rest/queries.md#2025-04-22_snippet_28

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import http.client
import json
import urllib.parse


connection = http.client.HTTPSConnection('YOUR.PARSE-SERVER.HERE', 443)
params = urllib.parse.urlencode({"where": json.dumps({
    "playerName": "Jonathan Walsh"
}),
"count": 1,
