TITLE: Implementing Session Restriction Check in Parse Cloud beforeSave Handler
DESCRIPTION: Cloud Code handler that prevents restricted sessions from modifying specific classes. It queries the session object using the user's session token and throws an error if the session is restricted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/rest/sessions.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
Parse.Cloud.beforeSave("MyClass", async request => {
  const user = request.user;
  const token = user.getSessionToken(); 
  const query = new Parse.Query(Parse.Session);
  query.equalTo('sessionToken', token);
  const session = await q.first({ useMasterKey: true });
  if (session.get('restricted')) {
      throw 'write operation not allowed';
  }
});
```

