TITLE: Defining GraphQL Configuration Interface in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: TypeScript interface defining the configuration options for Parse Server GraphQL schema customization. Includes settings for enabled/disabled classes, input/output fields, queries, and mutations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/graphql/customisation.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
interface ParseGraphQLConfiguration {
  enabledForClasses?: Array<string>;
  disabledForClasses?: Array<string>;
  classConfigs?: Array<{
    className: string;
    type?: {
      inputFields?: {
        create?: Array<string>;
        update?: Array<string>;
      };
      outputFields?: Array<string>;
      constraintFields?: Array<string>;
      sortFields?: {
        field: string;
        asc: boolean;
        desc: boolean;
      }[];
    };
    query?: {
      get?: boolean;
      find?: boolean;
      getAlias?: String;
      findAlias?: String;
    };
    mutation?: {
      create?: boolean;
      update?: boolean;
      destroy?: boolean;
      createAlias?: String,
      updateAlias?: String,
      destroyAlias?: String,
    };
  }>
}
```

