TITLE: Setting Group Permissions with ParseACL in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to create a group message with custom read and write permissions for multiple users. It iterates through a list of users and grants them individual access to the message object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/php/users.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$groupMessage = new ParseObject("Message");
$groupACL = new ParseACL();

// userList is an array with the users we are sending this message to.
for ($i = 0; $i < count($userList); $i++) {
  $groupACL->setReadAccess($userList[$i], true);
  $groupACL->setWriteAccess($userList[$i], true);
}

$groupMessage->setACL($groupACL);
$groupMessage->save();
```

