TITLE: Generic Node Query Across Multiple Types - GraphQL
DESCRIPTION: Utilizing type-specific fragments, this query demonstrates how to fetch a Node (either User or GameScore) by ID, with each fragment returning fields appropriate to the object type. This supports dynamic rendering of multiple types on the frontend, relying on the '__typename' discriminator.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/graphql/queries.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: GraphQL
CODE:
```
query genericGet {
  node(id: "X1VzZXI6Q1lMeWJYMjFjcw==") {
    id
    __typename
    ... on User {
      id
      username
    }
    ... on GameScore {
      playerName
      score
      cheatMode
    }
  }
}
```

