TITLE: AfterSave Comment Counter Webhook in Ruby
DESCRIPTION: Ruby webhook implementation for tracking comment counts after saving. Updates comment count in external data source.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/cloudcode/cloud-code-advanced.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
protect_from_forgery :except => :comments

def comments
  if request.headers['X-Parse-Webhook-Key'] != @webhook_key
    return render :nothing => true
  end

  comment = params[:object]
  if params[:triggerName] == "afterSave" && comment["className"] == "Comment"
    post = comment["post"]
    @post_model = Post.where("id = #{post["objectId"]}")
    @post_model.increment(:comments_count, 1)
    @post_model.save!
    return render :nothing => true
  end

  render :nothing => true
end
```

