TITLE: Implementing afterDelete Webhook Handler in Ruby
DESCRIPTION: Ruby implementation of an afterDelete webhook handler that decrements comment counts in an external SQL database when comments are deleted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/cloudcode/cloud-code-advanced.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
protect_from_forgery :except => :comments

def comments
  if request.headers['X-Parse-Webhook-Key'] != @webhook_key
    return render :nothing => true
  end

  comment = params[:object]
  if params[:triggerName] == "afterDelete" && comment["className"] == "Comment"
    @post_model = Post.where("id = #{comment['post']}")
    @post_model.decrement(:comments_count, 1)
    @post_model.save!
    return render :nothing => true
  end

  render :nothing => true
end
```

