TITLE: Implementing Customer Billing Webhook in Ruby
DESCRIPTION: Ruby webhook implementation for handling customer billing requests. Validates webhook key, processes chargeCustomer function, and enqueues billing jobs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/cloudcode/cloud-code-advanced.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
protect_from_forgery :except => :index

def index
  if request.headers['X-Parse-Webhook-Key'] !== @webhook_key
    return render :json => { :error => "Request Unauthorized"}
  end

  if params[:functionName] == "chargeCustomer" && params[:master] == true
    custom_params = params[:params]
    user_id = custom_params["userObjectId"]
    Resque.enqueue(BillingJob, user_id)
    return render :json => { :success => "User billed!" }
  end

  return render :json => { :error => "Unknown function"}
end
```

