TITLE: Querying Objects in a Bounding Box with Python
DESCRIPTION: Makes a GET request using Python to find places within a rectangular area defined by southwest and northeast coordinates using the $within and $box operators.
SOURCE: https://github.com/parse-community/docs/blob/gh-pages/_includes/rest/geopoints.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import http.client
import json
import urllib.parse


connection = http.client.HTTPSConnection('YOUR.PARSE-SERVER.HERE', 443)
params = urllib.parse.urlencode({"where": json.dumps({
    "location": {
        "$within": {
            "$box": [
                {
                    "__type": "GeoPoint",
                    "latitude": 37.71,
                    "longitude": -122.53
                },
                {
                    "__type": "GeoPoint",
                    "latitude": 30.82,
                    "longitude": -122.37
                }
            ]
        }
    }
})})
connection.connect()
connection.request('GET', '/parse/classes/PizzaPlaceObject?%s' % params, '', {
    "X-Parse-Application-Id": "${APPLICATION_ID}",
    "X-Parse-REST-API-Key": "${REST_API_KEY}"
})
result = json.loads(connection.getresponse().read())
print(result)
```

